    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - CHASSIS FEATURES - Reverse Motion
        Sensor - DIAGNOSTICS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DIAGNOSTICS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Should the reverse motion sensor fail to operate, the problem could be attributed to an open or
                shorted circuit or a faulty sensor or a fault back-up alarm.
            </para>
            <para>There are no diagnostic trouble codes associated with the Reverse motion sensor.</para>
            <para>For proper installation documentation, refer to the DS1500 Directional Sensor Installation and
                Operation Manual available through Electronic Controls Co. (ECCO).
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
